Project Overview
Analyzed Netflix's content offerings using a dataset of TV shows and movies
Created visualizations to gain insights into content types, ratings, duration, release years, and top-producing countries
Key Findings
Comparison of movie and TV show content on Netflix
Distribution of ratings across TV shows and movies
Movie duration analysis
Year-over-year trend of movie and TV show releases
Top 10 countries with the most content on Netflix
Visualizations
Bar chart comparing movie and TV show counts
Pie chart showing rating distribution
Histogram of movie durations
Scatter plot of movie releases over the years
Horizontal bar chart of top 10 content-producing countries
Subplots comparing movie and TV show releases over the years
Technologies Used
Python 3.x
Pandas for data manipulation and analysis
Matplotlib for data visualization
Dataset
Netflix titles dataset (netflix_titles.csv)
How to Run
Clone the repository
Install required libraries (pandas, matplotlib)
Run the Python script to generate visualizations
Files
netflix_analysis.py (or your script name): main analysis script
netflix_titles.csv: dataset file
*.png files: generated visualizations
Future Work
Analyze content trends over time
Explore correlations between ratings and other variables
Compare Netflix's content offerings to other streaming platforms
